    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p>At 14th level, the magic of the Feywild grants you the ability to travel mentally or physically through dreamlands.</p><p>When you finish a short rest, you can cast one of the following spells, without expending a spell slot or requiring material components: @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.dUu2htJQoxRXgxD2] (with you as the messenger), @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.OecyeJZgjK2ji9pq], or @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.GovMhwY2Z5VLeYWx].</p><p>This use of @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.GovMhwY2Z5VLeYWx] is special. Rather than opening a portal to a permanent @UUID[Compendium.renegados-compendium.magias.Item.GovMhwY2Z5VLeYWx], it opens a portal to the last location where you finished a long rest on your current plane of existence. If you haven't taken a long rest on your current plane, the spell fails but isn't wasted.</p><p>Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a long rest.</p></div>",
